Is this a serious release? Not really... Since so many of my 0.2mm nozzles on my Bambu A1 were failing, I thought maybe one could upcycle these as weapons in tanks. And while being on that, I decided to do that for empty ArmyPainter bottles, too. And since I was experimenting a bit with stuff, I decided to try to AI generate three more tanks. So here you are! 5 Tanks that you could play in your games (and I'd be happy if you did and showed me images), but it's quite questionable if you did.

Of course I forged them into a library for my customizer! Have fun combining them with my other scrap tanks!

Powered by Image-to-3D from MakerWorld (https://makerworld.com/makerlab/imageTo3d)

Happy Orktober! This final Orktober release combines some of the previous releases into one big print-paint&play army for grimdark future. 3000 Points of pure metal, all models having tough and a high defense, so if your enemy doesn't have that much deadly or armor penetration, you'd probably have a good time!

I once played this army online in my free wargaming simulator ( https://udos3dworld.com/WargamingSimulator/ ) against some lust daemons and seriously, it was a massacre, so my opponent resigned after round 2. I included all the assets you need to play this army, so you could just use the "Upload Whole Army" feature, and have everything added to the battlefield.

These are remixes from Vohvel's excellent originals:

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4862377

I've used some other bits and bobs also, such as JayMull420's glyphs and Alpokemon's quite frankly wonderful chibi tiger:

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4694469

https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:2391204

I did these a couple of years ago so I may have forgotten someone's bits: please let me know if so. I'm a bit of a noob with MeshMixer so, again, apologies if for anything messy. I've basically embedded guns in the front, added peg-turrets and given lots of glyph/no glyph [clean] options. They've all printed fine my end so fingers crossed yours. If you have problems with the pegs not fitting the holes properly then just resize the turrets a bit as some resins cure with odd dimensions. These are re-sized to what I think orks should roughly be on the Moonjammy scale (so 90% of Vohvel's originals)? Hope you enjoy using them to munch humies. Waaagh!

UPDATE: 2023-10-11
I didn't expect quite so many downloads so to I've done some extra bits last night that I was going to leave till Christmas. Essentially just some fiddling to create more variety (orks don't really do 'standardised', do they :) ?). More glyph options (the numbers correlate with those in JayMull420's pack for those wanting to fiddle more), some new turrets and, crucially, bolted versions of the dozer glyphs in addition to the welded. Thingiverse couldn't cope with one zip file so I've done three. Hope you enjoy them and any donations to the originators listed above, please, rather than me. Cheers.
